  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Low Code Engineer",
  "description": "<p>We are currently looking for <strong>a Low Code Engineer</strong> with <strong>minimum 3</strong> <strong>years of relevant experience</strong> specifically in <strong>SharePoint Online, Microsoft Power Apps and Microsoft Power Automate:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>RESPONSIBILITY</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><em><strong>Design, build, and deploy applications using low code/no code platforms</strong></em> such as <u><em>OutSystems, Mendix, Power Apps, or similar tools;</em></u></li>\n  <li><em><strong>Work closely with business analysts and stakeholders </strong></em>to understand business requirements and translate them into technical specifications;</li>\n  <li><em><strong>Develop automated workflows, forms, and integrations to streamline business processes and improve operational efficiency;</strong></em></li>\n  <li><em><strong>Conduct thorough testing of applications</strong></em> to ensure they meet functional and non-functional requirements;</li>\n  <li><em><strong>Maintain comprehensive documentation for developed applications</strong></em>, including <u><em>user guides, technical specifications, and support materials;</em></u></li>\n  <li><em><strong>Collaborate with cross-functional teams</strong></em>, including <u><em>IT, business units, and external vendors</em></u>, to deliver high-quality applications that meet business needs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS NEEDED</strong></u></p>\n<p>Degree or Diploma in Computer Science, Computer or Electronics Engineering, Information Technology or related disciplines.</p>\n<p><em><strong>3+ years of experience in application development</strong></em>, with a <em><strong>focus on low code/no code platforms</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>Familiar with Git</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><em><strong>Experience working in agile teams</strong></em> – TDD, Pair programming, Scrum, Continuous Integration</li>\n  <li><em><strong>Proven experience in developing and deploying applications with minimal coding;</strong></em></li>\n  <li><em><strong>Knowledge of web technologies</strong></em> (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) and <em><strong>database systems</strong></em> (SQL, NoSQL);</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with APIs and integrations with other enterprise systems;</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team;</li>\n  <li>Attention to detail and commitment to delivering high-quality solutions;</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills along with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Desirable Skill(s)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><em><strong>Familiarity with DevOps practices</strong></em>, including<u><em> CI / CD pipelines;</em></u></li>\n  <li><em><strong>Relevant certifications in low code / no code platforms.</strong></em></li>\n  <li><em><strong>Exposure to mobile application development</strong></em> will be an added <u><em>advantage.</em></u></li>\n  <li><em><strong>Hands-on configuration experience in administration setup and managing Low-code product and features,</strong></em> including but not limited to rules engine, workflow, processes logics, data validations screen flows and page layouts with products such as Salesforce, OutSystems, Mendix, Microsoft Power Apps, Appian, ServiceNow, Sharepoint Online, Dynamics 365.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Working Location : East Central </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>**We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes**</strong></em></p>\n<p><br></p>",
